# Build: My Cards Page (`app/(customer)/my-cards/page.js`)

## Context
Refer to CLAUDE.md for full project context, stack, folder structure, database schema, and Supabase client conventions before writing any code. Primary brand color is `emerald-600`. This page lives inside the customer layout shell — do not rebuild the sidebar or header.

---

## What to build

A page at `app/(customer)/my-cards/page.js` showing all NFC items assigned to the logged-in customer. This is a read-focused page — the customer cannot create or delete cards here, only view them and access the information needed to program them.

This is a **Client Component** (`'use client'`).

---

## Performance requirements

- Fetch all NFC items for the current user in a **single Supabase query** — include tap count per item using Supabase's count feature, not separate per-item requests
- On mount, immediately render skeleton cards while data loads — never a blank page or full-page spinner
- Clipboard copy operations must use the modern `navigator.clipboard.writeText()` API with a graceful fallback to `document.execCommand('copy')` for older browsers

---

## Page header

- **Left:** "My Cards" heading + muted subtitle "Your NFC products and profile links"
- **Right:** A muted stat chip: "X cards" — renders once data loads, skeleton while loading

---

## Card grid layout

Render each NFC item as a card. Layout: `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5`. Each card is self-contained — no table, no list rows.

### Each NFC item card

**Card header:**
- Product type icon — use a distinct lucide-react icon per type:
  - Card → `CreditCard`
  - Stand → `MonitorSmartphone`
  - Round Tag → `Disc`
- Product type label next to the icon: "NFC Card", "NFC Stand", "NFC Round Tag"
- Status badge top-right — shadcn/ui `Badge`:
  - Active → emerald, "Active"
  - Inactive → gray, "Inactive"

**Profile URL section:**
A clearly labelled block inside the card:
- Label: "Your profile URL" in small muted uppercase text
- A read-only input field containing the full URL: `https://beemhive.com/t/{slug}`
- A copy icon button (`Copy` from lucide-react) on the right edge of the input. On click:
  - Copy URL to clipboard
  - Icon changes to `Check` for 1.5 seconds then reverts
  - Show a shadcn/ui `Toast`: "Copied to clipboard"
- Below the input: a muted caption "Write this URL to your NFC card using NFC Tools"

**Tap stats strip:**
A subtle horizontal strip inside the card, separated by a `Separator`:
- `MousePointerClick` icon + "X total taps" — all-time tap count for this specific card
- `Zap` icon + "X taps today" — taps where `created_at` is today (compute client-side from fetched data, not a separate query)
- `Clock` icon + "Last tap: X ago" — using `formatRelativeTime()` from `lib/utils.js`. If no taps yet: "No taps yet"

**Action buttons row** at the bottom of the card:
Two buttons side by side, full width split equally:

1. "View Profile" — `ExternalLink` icon, outline variant. Opens `https://beemhive.com/t/{slug}` in a new tab.

2. "NFC Setup" — `Smartphone` icon, ghost variant. Expands the NFC Tools instruction panel below (accordion-style toggle). Chevron icon rotates on expand.

**NFC Tools instruction panel** (collapsed by default, smooth `transition-all duration-200` expand):

A soft `amber-50` (light mode) / `amber-950` (dark mode) instruction box with `amber-200` border. Content:

```
How to program your NFC card

1. Download "NFC Tools" — free on iOS and Android
2. Open NFC Tools → tap "Write" → tap "Add a record" → select "URL/URI"
3. Paste your profile URL:
   [URL displayed in a copyable code block]
4. Tap "Write / XX bytes" then hold your phone against your NFC card
5. Done — your card now opens your Beem Hive profile when tapped
```

The URL inside the instruction panel has its own copy button. Below the instructions, a small note in muted text: "You only need to do this once per card."

